        }
        .element {
            width: 40px;
            height: 40px;
            margin: 0 4px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            color: white;
            font-weight: bold;
            border-radius: 4px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s, transform 0.3s;
        }
        .button-container {
            text-align: center;
        }
        button {
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin: 8px 0;
        }
        button:disabled {
            background-color: #ccc;
            cursor: not-allowed;
        }
        #info {
            margin-top: 16px;
            font-size: 14px;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Interactive Selection Sort</h1>
        <div class="array" id="arrayContainer"></div>
        <div class="button-container">
            <button id="startSort">Start Sorting</button>
            <button id="reset">Reset</button>
        </div>
        <div id="info">Click "Start Sorting" to see the Selection Sort in action!</div>
    </div>

    <script>
        const arrayContainer = document.getElementById('arrayContainer');
        const startButton = document.getElementById('startSort');
        const resetButton = document.getElementById('reset');
        let array = [];

        function generateRandomArray(size) {
            array = Array.from({ length: size }, () => Math.floor(Math.random() * 100) + 1);
            displayArray();
        }

        function displayArray() {
            arrayContainer.innerHTML = '';
            array.forEach((value, index) => {
                const element = document.createElement('div');
                element.className = 'element';
                element.style.backgroundColor = '#007bff';
                element.textContent = value;
                arrayContainer.appendChild(element);
            });
        }

        async function selectionSort() {
            startButton.disabled = true;
            for (let i = 0; i < array.length - 1; i++) {
                let minIndex = i;
                for (let j = i + 1; j < array.length; j++) {
                    if (array[j] < array[minIndex]) {
                        minIndex = j;
                    }
                    await highlightElements(i, minIndex, j);
                }
                if (minIndex !== i) {
                    swap(i, minIndex);
                }
                await displayArray();
            }
            startButton.disabled = false;
            document.getElementById('info').textContent = "Sorting complete!";
        }

        function swap(i, j) {
            const temp = array[i];
            array[i] = array[j];
            array[j] = temp;
        }

        async function highlightElements(currentIndex, minIndex, comparisonIndex) {
            const elements = document.querySelectorAll('.element');
            elements[currentIndex].style.backgroundColor = '#f39c12'; // Current sorted portion
            elements[minIndex].style.backgroundColor = '#27ae60'; // Minimum element
            elements[comparisonIndex].style.backgroundColor = '#c0392b'; // Element being compared
            await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 500));
            elements[currentIndex].style.backgroundColor = '#007bff';
            elements[minIndex].style.backgroundColor = '#007bff';
            elements[comparisonIndex].style.backgroundColor = '#007bff';
        }

        resetButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
            generateRandomArray(10);
            document.getElementById('info').textContent = "Click 'Start Sorting' to see the Selection Sort in action!";
            startButton.disabled = false;
        });

        startButton.addEventListener('click', selectionSort);

        // Initialize the array
        generateRandomArray(10);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Breakdown of the Design:

1. **Concept Title:** 
   - "Interactive Selection Sort"

2. **Learning Objective:** 
   - Users will understand how the Selection Sort algorithm works visually, analyzing the process of finding the minimum element and swapping it with the current element in an array.

3. **Interaction Design:** 
   - The user can click the "Start Sorting" button to see the Selection Sort in action. 
   - Each step will be visually represented, highlighting the current index, minimum index found, and element being compared.
   - There’s a "Reset" button to regenerate the array for another sorting demonstration.
   - Animations provide visual feedback that reinforces the learning experience.

4. **Layout Description:** 
   - The page is centered and padded to maintain a clean look. 
   - The array holds colored boxes representing the values, laid out in a flexbox for alignment. 
   - Interactive buttons are centrally aligned below the array for easy access.
   - The information text at the bottom gives users prompts, helping guide their understanding.
   - The safe area margins of **24 px** are maintained uniformly, and all interactive elements are spaced by **16 px**.

### Accessibility and Responsiveness:
- The buttons have clear labels and are easily identifiable, ensuring users can navigate effectively.
- The layout is designed to be responsive, with flexbox handling array positioning, which adapts to varying screen sizes.

### Conclusion:
This interactive module effectively teaches Selection Sort by utilizing visual cues and responsive animations, ensuring an engaging user experience while promoting a deeper understanding of the algorithm.

