Heap Sort Interactive Module

#### Learning Objective
Users will understand how the Heap Sort algorithm works by visualizing the process of building a heap and sorting an array step-by-step. They will experience the creation and transformation of a bar graph representation of the array data.

#### Interaction Design
- **Generate Array Button**: When clicked, random numbers between 1 and 100 will be generated and displayed as bars in a visualization area. This represents the unsorted array.
- **Sort Array Button**: Activates the sorting of the generated array using the Heap Sort algorithm. As the sort progresses, the heights of the bars will animate to reflect the changing state of the array.
- Visual updates will include the height of bars changing in real-time, which helps users connect the algorithm's steps to their visual representation.

#### Layout Description
- **Body**: Provides a clean, white canvas with a gray background.
- **Container**: Centers content with 24 px margins, 16 px spacing between controls and elements, maintaining a structured layout.
- **Visualization Section**: The bars representing the numbers are centered and spaced appropriately for clarity.
- **Controls**: Positioned at the bottom of the container for easy access, with buttons styled for visibility and usability.
- **Accessibility and Responsiveness**: All elements are accessible via keyboard (buttons) and properly labeled with clear visual feedback. The design scales well to smaller screens while maintaining spacing.

This module delivers an engaging and intuitive experience for users to learn about Heap Sort through hands-on interaction and visual feedback.

