Users will fully grasp the Knapsack Problem's concept by interactively selecting items to add to a virtual knapsack, observing how their selections affect the overall value and weight. By the end of the module, users should understand the trade-offs involved in optimizing for maximum value within a weight limit.

#### Interaction Design:
1. **Item Selection**: Users can select or deselect items from a list of items, each with a specified value and weight. Clicking an item toggles selection.
2. **Knapsack Capacity Input**: Users input a maximum weight capacity through an input field. An “Update” button will apply this capacity to the simulation.
3. **Calculation and Display**: When items are selected and the capacity is set, clicking an “Calculate” button will trigger an algorithm to determine which items maximize the value without exceeding the weight limit. The results will be displayed below.
4. **Visual Feedback**: Selected items will be visually highlighted. The total value and weight of selected items will be updated live as the user toggles items. An animation will show the optimal selections when calculated, clearly indicating which items were chosen.

#### Layout Description:
- **Viewport Margin**: Use a safe area of 24 px on all sides.
- **Header Section**: At the top center, the title “Understanding the Knapsack Problem” will be prominently displayed in large font.

- **Item Selection Section (Left Side)**: This section will list items vertically.
  - Each item will be in a card format, showing its name, value, and weight.
  - A checkbox for selection will be adjacent to each item. Spacing of 16 px will be maintained between items for clear separation.

- **Capacity Input Section (Right Side)**: 
  - An input field for the maximum weight capacity will be centrally placed.
  - Below the input, an “Update” button will trigger the recalculation.

- **Calculation Section (Bottom)**: 
  - A button labeled “Calculate” will be centrally located.
  - Below this, a summary area will display the total selected value and weight after the calculation, with an animation showing which items were selected as optimal choices.

